76561197991605397,Recommended,302970,12191449,"Posted: 22 September, 2014",all,Stevorino,"I'm a pretty avid fan of tower defense titles and Radiant Defense was a pleasant surprise.  If I were giving it a grade on a scale from 1-10, I'd give it a solid 7.  It doesn't do anything genre-defining like Orcs Must Die or Kingdom Rush, but it does put the standard tower defense pieces together well to create a challenging experience.If you research this game for more than 30 seconds, you'll see that people complain/rave that it is very difficult.  It is definately a very challenging tower defense game, easily one of the hardest I have played.  Unfortunately, the difficulty often comes as a result of poor wave balancing.  The difficulty really gives very low margin for error, causing you to not experiment too much in the obvious formula to success.Also, unlike a lot of the best tower defense games, there's really no tower-progression or leveling up through the campaign - you have access to all of the towers right away.  This creates somewhat of a rinse-repeat feeling by halfway through the game that never goes away as nothing very new presents itself throughout the entire game except stronger and stronger waves.I would definitely recommend it to genre fans like me looking for yet another Tower defense game to play.  For all others, I'd suggest first knocking out genre classics like Orcs Must Die, Dungeon Defenders, Kingdom Rush, and Bloons TD before spending your time on this title."
76561198007447880,Recommended,302970,11575444,"Posted: 6 August, 2014",all,duegrom,"I have always been a fan of tower defense games and on the surface this seemed like a well put together attempt.However, what starts out as pretty standard fare becomes one of the most challenging games I have ever played. At the end of each wave interest is applied to the total amount of money you have left. This leads to many instances where you think you are doing ok but then you hit a brick wall. The only way of progressing is to start again and make sure you don't overspend too early. This creates a unique challenge where you have to very carefully monitor whether you need to spend the money or not. I spent several days, and hundreds of attempts on some levels to get them finished. Mastering the interest mechanism is absolutely critical to completing some of the more challenging levels, and it is clear that the developers must have spent an age play testing it.Superb"
